
Function: MINUS

Syntax:   (MINUS arg1)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - a number.

Returns:

 The negative of arg1 (i.e. the value of arg1 multiplied by -1).

Processing:

 If arg1 is positive, the corresponding negative number of the same
 type is returned.  Otherwise, the corresponding positive number of
 the same type is returned.

Errors signaled:

 Non-numeric argument.

Notes:

Examples:

 (MINUS 0)              ==> 0
 (MINUS 0.0)            ==> 0.0
 (MINUS 0.0F0)          ==> 0.0F0
 (MINUS 2)              ==> -2
 (MINUS -3)             ==> 3
 (MINUS 1.5)            ==> -1.5
 (MINUS 1.5F0)          ==> -1.5F0
 (MINUS -1.5)           ==> 1.5
 (MINUS -1.5F0)         ==> 1.5F0
 (MINUS 2147483648)     ==> -21
 (MINUS -2147483648)    ==> 21
 (MINUS 1000000000000)  ==> -10000
 (MINUS -1000000000000) ==> 10000

